Renaissance Credit, the retail
banking arm of Renaissance Capital Financial Holdings Ltd., a
Russian emerging-markets bank, said it achieved the same
profitability in 2010 as before the financial crisis.  The bank, the parent company of which is half-owned by
billionaire  Mikhail Prokhorov , reported, in an e-mailed
statement, net income for the year of 1.6 billion rubles ($57
million), exceeding the 2008 profit of 1.5 billion rubles. In
2009, Renaissance Credit posted a net loss of 4.23 billion
rubles.  The bank issued new loans worth 22.8 billion rubles in
2010, a 530 percent increase over 2009.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Henry Meyer in Moscow at 
